title: Conquering Florida: Wakeboarding in Orlando
text:
Updated: 2:48 p.m. Tuesday, Aug. 25, 2015 | Posted: 6:19 a.m. Tuesday, Aug. 25, 2015 Conquering Florida: Wakeboarding in Orlando In Partnership with VisitFlorida.com 
Known for his greatness in motocross, Florida native Ricky Carmichael retires his bike for the day to conquer Florida by testing his wakeboarding skills at Orlando Watersports Complex . Ricky meets up with fellow Fox athletes, four-time world champion Shaun Murray and inventor of the 1260 Danny Harf to learn the ins and outs of OWCâ€™s cable park. Home to almost 90 percent of professional wake-boarders, Orlando, Florida is the premier location to experience and learn this amazing action sport. Special thanks to Team Nautique , Team Hyperlite and Sony ActionCam for helping bring this episode to life.
